### Ignore Background Transactions (Node.js)

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

This snippet shows how to use the `setIgnoreTransaction()` API method in the New Relic Node.js agent to ignore background transactions. This is useful for preventing the agent from reporting metrics for operations that are not considered core business transactions, helping to keep monitoring data clean. It requires the New Relic agent to be initialized.

```javascript
const newrelic = require('newrelic');

// ... when starting a background task ...
newrelic.setIgnoreTransaction(true);
// ... perform background task ...
newrelic.setIgnoreTransaction(false); // Reset if necessary for subsequent transactions
```

