### Get Browser Timing Header - Node.js

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

Introduced in v1.23.1, the `newrelic.getBrowserTimingHeader()` API now includes the full transaction name. This ensures correct cross-linking between Browser Monitoring and APM transactions. This function is called within your Node.js application to obtain the necessary header script.

```javascript
const newrelic = require('newrelic');

// In your Express or other Node.js app:
