### Custom Metrics Naming in Node.js Agent

Source: https://github.com/newrelic/node-newrelic/blob/main/NEWS.md

Custom metrics recorded via `recordMetric` and `incrementMetric` in the Node.js agent now automatically prepend 'Custom/'. If 'Custom/' is manually prepended, it will result in a double prefix. This change affects how custom metrics are named and should be managed in existing applications.

```javascript
// Old behavior (manual prepending):
api.recordMetric('Custom/MyMetric', 10);

// New behavior (automatic prepending):
// If 'Custom/' is manually prepended, it results in 'Custom/Custom/'
api.recordMetric('MyMetric', 10); // Results in 'Custom/MyMetric'
api.recordMetric('Custom/MyMetric', 10); // Results in 'Custom/Custom/MyMetric'
```

